    <item>
      <title>OWASP PTK Options</title>
      <link>/docs/desktop/addons/owasp-ptk/ptk-options/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/desktop/addons/owasp-ptk/ptk-options/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;owasp-ptk-options&#34;&gt;OWASP PTK Options&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;active-scan&#34;&gt;Active Scan &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34; href=&#34;#active-scan&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;fill-current o-60 hover-accent-color-light&#34; height=&#34;22px&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;22px&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;On the &lt;strong&gt;Active Scan&lt;/strong&gt; tab, &lt;strong&gt;Enable Active Scan Rule&lt;/strong&gt; controls whether the PTK active scan rule runs during ZAP active scans.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>OWASP PTK Active Scan Rule</title>
      <link>/docs/desktop/addons/owasp-ptk/ptk-ascan/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/desktop/addons/owasp-ptk/ptk-ascan/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;owasp-ptk-active-scan-rule&#34;&gt;OWASP PTK Active Scan Rule&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This add-on provides a single active scan rule, &lt;strong&gt;PTK Scan Rules&lt;/strong&gt; , that drives browsers against the target host so that PTK&amp;rsquo;s in-browser engines (SAST, IAST, DAST) run as the browsers traverses the application.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is at an early stage and more changes are planned, and for that reason is is disabled by default.&#xA;It can be enabled via the &lt;a href=&#34;/docs/desktop/addons/owasp-ptk/ptk-options/&#34;&gt;OWASP PTK Options&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;or via the command line: &lt;code&gt;-config ptk.activescan.rule.enabled=true&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
